{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "", "ts": "2026-05-18T15:11:20+00:00", "time": "18:11:20"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "  ▶ Read  C:\\CCoreAI\\DirectClaude\\DirectClaude\\projects\\15-ble-scan\\Core\\Src\\fc41d.c", "ts": "2026-05-18T15:11:20+00:00", "time": "18:11:20"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "", "ts": "2026-05-18T15:11:20+00:00", "time": "18:11:20"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "  ▶ Read  C:\\CCoreAI\\DirectClaude\\DirectClaude\\projects\\15-ble-scan\\Core\\Inc\\fc41d.h", "ts": "2026-05-18T15:11:20+00:00", "time": "18:11:20"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "", "ts": "2026-05-18T15:11:23+00:00", "time": "18:11:23"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "  ▶ Read  C:\\CCoreAI\\DirectClaude\\DirectClaude\\projects\\15-ble-scan\\Core\\Src\\main.c", "ts": "2026-05-18T15:11:23+00:00", "time": "18:11:23"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "There are **three separate reasons** stacking against you, all visible in the code:", "ts": "2026-05-18T15:11:54+00:00", "time": "18:11:54"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "---", "ts": "2026-05-18T15:11:54+00:00", "time": "18:11:54"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "### 1. FC41DAAR03A09 firmware sends no advertising data in the URC", "ts": "2026-05-18T15:11:54+00:00", "time": "18:11:54"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "The actual URC is only 3 fields:", "ts": "2026-05-18T15:11:54+00:00", "time": "18:11:54"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "```", "ts": "2026-05-18T15:11:54+00:00", "time": "18:11:54"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "+QBLESCAN:,1,1f953971eae5", "ts": "2026-05-18T15:11:54+00:00", "time": "18:11:54"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "```", "ts": "2026-05-18T15:11:54+00:00", "time": "18:11:54"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "No 4th field → `adv_hex[0] == '\\0'` → `extract_ble_name()` is never called (`fc41d.c:287`). The AT manual describes an `<adv_data>` field but this firmware version simply omits it.", "ts": "2026-05-18T15:11:54+00:00", "time": "18:11:54"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "### 2. Active scanning is unsupported on this firmware", "ts": "2026-05-18T15:11:54+00:00", "time": "18:11:54"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "`AT+QBLESCANPARAM=1,100,50` returns `ERROR` (locked in STATE.md). Active scan would cause the FC41D to send scan requests, prompting devices to reply with **scan response PDUs** that typically carry the full device name (AD type 0x09). Since that command fails, the module stays in passive mode — no scan responses, no names.", "ts": "2026-05-18T15:11:54+00:00", "time": "18:11:54"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "### 3. All detected devices use random/private addresses (type=1)", "ts": "2026-05-18T15:11:54+00:00", "time": "18:11:54"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "STATE.md says all 3 seen devices are type=1 (phones in privacy mode). The GATT name resolution path (`FC41D_BLE_GetName`) is only attempted for `addr_type == 0` (`main.c:87`). Type=1 devices reject incoming connections, so skipping them is correct — but it means the GATT fallback never fires.", "ts": "2026-05-18T15:11:54+00:00", "time": "18:11:54"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "---", "ts": "2026-05-18T15:11:54+00:00", "time": "18:11:54"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "**Net result:** every path to reading a name is blocked simultaneously for type=1 devices on this firmware version.", "ts": "2026-05-18T15:11:54+00:00", "time": "18:11:54"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "**What would actually fix it:**", "ts": "2026-05-18T15:11:54+00:00", "time": "18:11:54"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "| Fix | What it enables |", "ts": "2026-05-18T15:11:54+00:00", "time": "18:11:54"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "|---|---|", "ts": "2026-05-18T15:11:54+00:00", "time": "18:11:54"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "| Firmware upgrade to a version that includes adv_hex in the URC | Names from passive advertising data |", "ts": "2026-05-18T15:11:54+00:00", "time": "18:11:54"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "| Quectel supporting `AT+QBLESCANPARAM` active scan | Names from scan response PDUs |", "ts": "2026-05-18T15:11:54+00:00", "time": "18:11:54"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "| Test with a type=0 device (e.g. Samsung SmartTag button press) | GATT path works, reads Device Name from handle 0x0003 |", "ts": "2026-05-18T15:11:54+00:00", "time": "18:11:54"}
{"type": "text", "stream": "stdout", "text": "The code paths are all correctly implemented — the limitation is the FC41DAAR03A09 firmware stripping the advertising payload from its URCs before your parser can see it.", "ts": "2026-05-18T15:11:54+00:00", "time": "18:11:54"}
